      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CORVIGLIA (5) narrowly on top in a tough affair. He got home strongly over this track and distance last time out, settling too far back from a wide gate. He draws poorly again here but this race doesn't look overly strong and he can look to find the best lanes out wider. SACRE BLEU (3) just found one better last start at Cranbourne when tracking the pace and working home well. He can look to push forward and will take some beating. GOLDEN MASK (1) is an 18 start maiden who has been thereabouts of late without being able to break through. He was just fair last time but has been freshened since and can give a sight. COLD AZA BEER (4) is lightly raced and was a bit better here last time with each way claims. CHERON FINALE (8) next best off an even run at Pakenham.",
